      <a href="https://book.douban.com/review/1522605/" class="title-link">告诉你什么是理性与批判</a>
      <div class="toggle_review right">        <a href="javascript:;" id="toggle-1522605"class="indicator unfold j" title="展开全文">        </a>
      </div>
    </h3>
    

<div class="header-more">
    <a class="author-avatar" href="https://www.douban.com/people/guugue/"><img width="48" height="48" src="https://img3.doubanio.com/icon/u2960510-2.jpg"></a>
    <a href="https://www.douban.com/people/guugue/" class="author">
      <span property="v:reviewer">阿古</span>
    </a>    <span property="v:rating" class="allstar50 main-title-rating" title="力荐"></span>
  <span property="v:dtreviewed" content="2008-10-12"
      class="main-meta">2008-10-12 17:37:45</span>
</div>

  </header>

        <div class="main-bd">
          <div id="review_1522605_short" class="review-short">
            <div class="short-content">
                  这本书对我的价值观念影响很大。可以说是它梳理了我的思维，虽然波普尔的观点只是一家之言，却实在是对理性的一次集中的表达与赞美。对于让我认识到什么是“真”有着特殊的意义。至于什么是善，自然要在别的地方寻找。

                    <a class="pl" href="https://book.douban.com/review/1522605/#comments">(1回应)</a>
                  <div class="more-info pl clearfix">
                    <span class="left">7有用 / 1没用</span>
                  </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div id="review_1522605_full" class="hidden">
            <div id="review_1522605_full_content" class="full-content"></div>
          </div>
        </div>
    </div>
  </div>





</div>










